External morphology:—see 
<bibRefCitation id="6F774FCAFB3DFFAFC696B1B4FD02FC05" author="Mayrhofer, H. &amp; Poelt J." box="[453,752,932,958]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" pagination="781 - 798" refId="ref7115" refString="Mayrhofer, H. &amp; Poelt J. (1978) Phaeorrhiza, eine neue Gattung der Physciaceae (Lichenes). Nova Hedwigia 30: 781 - 798. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / nova. hedwigia / 30 / 1979 / 781" type="journal article" year="1978">Mayrhofer &amp; Poelt (1978)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="43FC61B0FB3DFFAFC7EEB1D8FC34FB2C" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="0B59323BFB3DFFAFC7EEB1D8FC34FB2C" blockId="3.[136,1452,932,1175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC7EEB1D8FEBAFC59" authorityName="H. Mayrhofer &amp; Poelt" authorityYear="1979" box="[189,328,968,994]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Phaeorrhiza" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC7EEB1D8FEBAFC59" box="[189,328,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">Phaeorrhiza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a squamulose to subfoliose thallus, brown rhizohyphae on the lower side of the squamules, and the 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC630B1FCFE1BFBBD" authorityName="Trevisan" authorityYear="1857" box="[355,489,1004,1030]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Caliciaceae" genus="Beltraminia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC630B1FCFE1BFBBD" box="[355,489,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">Beltraminia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus id="D45D8C99FB3DFFAFC6A3B1FDFDD0FBBC" box="[496,546,1005,1031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">type</typeStatus>
ascospores (
<bibRefCitation id="6F774FCAFB3DFFAFC5FCB1FCFC3FFBBD" author="Mayrhofer, H. &amp; Poelt J." box="[687,973,1004,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" pagination="781 - 798" refId="ref7115" refString="Mayrhofer, H. &amp; Poelt J. (1978) Phaeorrhiza, eine neue Gattung der Physciaceae (Lichenes). Nova Hedwigia 30: 781 - 798. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / nova. hedwigia / 30 / 1979 / 781" type="journal article" year="1978">Mayrhofer &amp; Poelt, 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6F774FCAFB3DFFAFC48BB1FCFB82FBBD" author="Sheard, J. W." box="[984,1136,1004,1030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" pagination="9 - 10" refId="ref7541" refString="Sheard, J. W. (2010) The lichen genus Rinodina (Lecanoromycetidae, Physciaceae) in North America, north of Mexico. NRC Research Press, Ottawa, pp. 9 - 10." type="book chapter" year="2010">Sheard, 2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC3D1B1FCFAF0FBBD" box="[1154,1282,1004,1030]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Anaptychia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC3D1B1FCFAF0FBBD" box="[1154,1282,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">Anaptychia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC264B1FCFA5EFBBD" authorityName="Poelt" authorityYear="1965" box="[1335,1452,1004,1030]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Physconia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC264B1FCFA5EFBBD" box="[1335,1452,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">Physconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC681B600FDAFFB91" authorityName="H. Mayrhofer &amp; Poelt" authorityYear="1979" box="[466,605,1040,1066]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Phaeorrhiza" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC681B600FDAFFB91" box="[466,605,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">Phaeorrhiza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6F774FCAFB3DFFAFC53CB600FC9EFB91" author="Lohtander, K. &amp; Kallersjo, M. &amp; Moberg, R. &amp; Tehler A." box="[623,876,1040,1067]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" pagination="728 - 735" refId="ref6985" refString="Lohtander, K., Kallersjo, M., Moberg, R. &amp; Tehler A. (2000) The family Physciaceae in Fennoscandia: phylogeny inferred from ITS sequences. Mycologia 92 (4): 728 - 735. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.2000.12061212" type="journal article" year="2000">
Lohtander 
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC5BAB601FCD0FB91" box="[745,802,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">et al.</emphasis>
, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6F774FCAFB3DFFAFC424B600FBAFFB91" author="Grube, M. &amp; Arup, U." box="[887,1117,1040,1066]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" pagination="63 - 72" refId="ref6213" refString="Grube, M. &amp; Arup, U. (2001) Molecular and morphological evolution in the Physciaceae (Lecanorales, lichenized Ascomycotina), with special emphasis on the genus Rinodina. Lichenologist 33 (1): 63 - 72. https: // doi. org / 10.1006 / lich. 2000.0297" type="journal article" year="2001">Grube &amp; Arup 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6F774FCAFB3DFFAFC33BB600FACEFB91" author="Helms, G. &amp; Friedl, T. &amp; Rambold, G." box="[1128,1340,1040,1067]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" pagination="1078 - 1099" refId="ref6562" refString="Helms, G., Friedl, T. &amp; Rambold, G. (2003) Phylogenetic relationships of the Physciaceae inferred from rDNA sequence data and selected phenotypic characters. Mycologia 95 (6): 1078 - 1099. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3761914" type="journal article" year="2003">
Helms 
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC3EAB601FB00FB91" box="[1209,1266,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">et al.</emphasis>
, 2003
</bibRefCitation>
), but they differ by having a foliose thallus. Besides, some terrestrial taxa of 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC4D5B624FBFDFBF5" box="[902,1039,1076,1102]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Physciaceae</taxonomicName>
might bemorphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC7DBB648FEE3FBC9" authorityName="H. Mayrhofer &amp; Poelt" authorityYear="1979" box="[136,273,1112,1138]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Phaeorrhiza" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Phaeorrhiza</taxonomicName>
, such as 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC62BB648FD56FBC9" authority="Tomin." authorityName="Tomin." box="[376,676,1112,1138]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Rinodina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC62BB648FDBEFBC9" box="[376,588,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">Rinodina terrestris</emphasis>
Tomin.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CCE649B8FB3DFFAFC58FB648FB8FFBC9" authority="(Sommerf.) Arnold" authorityName="Arnold" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Sommerf." box="[732,1149,1112,1139]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Rinodina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Caliciales" pageId="3" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="roscida">
<emphasis id="3992EE29FB3DFFAFC58FB648FC6CFBC9" box="[732,926,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">Rinodina roscida</emphasis>
(Sommerf.) Arnold
</taxonomicName>
etc., but those species can be distinguished by the lack of rhizohyphae and different ascospore 
<typeStatus id="D45D8C99FB3DFFAFC4D0B66DFC30FB2C" box="[899,962,1149,1175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="231">types</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
